#: cefr-bo_pragmatic-flexibility_endocx_en.txt:2
msgid "Flexibility"
msgstr ""

#: cefr-bo_pragmatic-flexibility_endocx_en.txt:6
msgid ""
"C2_Shows great flexibility in reformulating ideas in differing"
"linguistic forms to give emphasis, differentiate according to the"
"situation, interlocutor, etc. and to eliminate ambiguity."
msgstr ""

#: cefr-bo_pragmatic-flexibility_endocx_en.txt:10
msgid ""
"C1_Can make a positive impact on an intended audience by effectively"
"varying style of expression and sentence length, use of advanced"
"vocabulary and word order."
msgstr ""

#: cefr-bo_pragmatic-flexibility_endocx_en.txt:13
msgid ""
"Can modify their expression to express degrees of commitment or"
"hesitation, confidence or uncertainty."
msgstr ""

#: cefr-bo_pragmatic-flexibility_endocx_en.txt:17
msgid ""
"B2+_Can adjust what they say and the means of expressing it to the"
"situation and the recipient and adopt a level of formality appropriate"
"to the circumstances."
msgstr ""

#: cefr-bo_pragmatic-flexibility_endocx_en.txt:20
msgid ""
"B2_Can adjust to the changes of direction, style and emphasis normally"
"found in conversation."
msgstr ""

#: cefr-bo_pragmatic-flexibility_endocx_en.txt:22
msgid "Can vary formulation of what they want to say."
msgstr ""

#: cefr-bo_pragmatic-flexibility_endocx_en.txt:24
msgid "Can reformulate an idea to emphasise or explain a point."
msgstr ""

#: cefr-bo_pragmatic-flexibility_endocx_en.txt:27
msgid ""
"B1_Can adapt their expression to deal with less routine, even difficult,"
"situations."
msgstr ""

#: cefr-bo_pragmatic-flexibility_endocx_en.txt:30
msgid ""
"Can exploit a wide range of simple language flexibly to express much of"
"what they want."
msgstr ""

#: cefr-bo_pragmatic-flexibility_endocx_en.txt:33
msgid ""
"A2_Can adapt well-rehearsed, memorised, simple phrases to particular"
"circumstances through limited lexical substitution."
msgstr ""

#: cefr-bo_pragmatic-flexibility_endocx_en.txt:36
msgid ""
"Can expand learnt phrases through simple recombinations of their"
"elements."
msgstr ""

